# Design — {{COMPANY_NAME}}

The canonical visual identity registry for {{COMPANY_NAME}}.
Source of truth for tokens, brand language, asset pointers, and
collateral specs.

> Discipline: see `.claude/design.md` (kit-managed) for the
> validation pattern, source-of-truth discipline, and cadence.

## What's here

| File | Holds |
|---|---|
| [`brand.md`](brand.md) | Color palette (hex codes), typography (families, scale), spacing scale, voice + tone. The high-level identity. |
| [`assets.md`](assets.md) | Asset registry — pointers to canonical asset files (logos, icons, illustrations) in design tools (Figma, Drive, etc.) with version + owner. |
| [`materials.md`](materials.md) | Collateral specs — business cards, letterhead, email signatures, presentation templates, swag. |
| [`mobile.md`](mobile.md) | Mobile graphics package — app icons, splash screens, in-app artwork specs. |
| [`web.md`](web.md) | Web design system specs — components, page templates, icon set. |

## When to update

- **Token / palette / typography change** → edit `brand.md`, file
  an ADR (`/decision`) explaining why, open a migration
  (`/migration`) if sub-repos need to update.
- **New canonical asset** (new logo variant, new icon set) → add
  to `assets.md` with the canonical URL.
- **New collateral type** (new business card variant, new email
  template) → add to `materials.md`.
- **Asset version bump** (logo refresh) → bump version in
  `assets.md` with a date stamp; AUDIT entry with 🎨.

## What this is NOT

- Not a Figma / Sketch / Adobe replacement — design tools are the
  right place for high-fidelity work.
- Not a deliverable ("brand guidelines.pdf") — it's the working
  source. Deliverables are produced FROM here.
- Not marketing copy — campaign-specific copy lives wherever
  marketing keeps it.

## Sources outside this directory

If high-fidelity assets exist in design tools, point at them from
`assets.md`. Common pointers:

- Figma project URL
- Drive folder URL
- Brand portal URL
- Notion page URL

The orchestrator stays markdown-only. Big binaries (PSD, AI, large
PNGs) don't get committed here — they live where they belong, with
pointers from this directory.

Small canonical assets (SVG logo, favicon, app icon at one or two
canonical sizes) MAY be committed under `design/assets/` for
git-diffable reference. Decide per asset based on diff usefulness.

